title: Episode 99 - Prelude To The Hungarian Revolution 1956
itunes:author: The History of the Cold War Podcast
itunes:summary: In this episode we explore the events leading up to the Hungarian Revolution of 1956. We examine Hungary's role in the second World War and how it became a Socalist state following the Second World War under the leadership of  Matyas Rakosi.
